            <subject>Adding a Relay Harness</subject>
        </subjectgroup>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>A relay harness is available through service parts to facilitate repairs or to add a relay in a
                    circuit or system to reduce current through switches, wiring, etc.
                </para>
                <para>To assist service technician installation,
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9608021">Figure 1</hotlnk>
                    identifies the circuit wires and location on relay connector body as viewed from the cable insertion
                    end.
                </para>
                <figure id="f9608021" figsize="pg-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G9608021.webp" type="webp" resolution="150"/>
                    <caption>Figure 1. Typical Circuit</caption>
                </figure>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
